<chapter xml:id="campus_type" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"  version="5.0">
    <info>
        <title>Campus Type</title>
    </info>
    <para>Administration > Identity > Reference > Campus Type</para>
    <para>When the user selects <emphasis role="bold">Campus Type</emphasis> from the <emphasis
            role="bold">Administration</emphasis> menu tab, the system displays the Campus Type
        Lookup. From this screen, the user may either create a new type or search for an existing
        type. This defines the valid types of campuses that can be selected when creating a new
        campus.</para>
    <para>After performing a search based on user-specified criteria, the system displays a results
        table. The user may then choose to edit or copy a retrieved record.</para>
    <para>After the user selects <emphasis role="bold">create new</emphasis>, <emphasis role="bold"
            >edit</emphasis>, or <emphasis role="bold">copy</emphasis>, the system displays the
        Campus Type Maintenance document. This document allows users to add and maintain campus
        types. </para>
    <note><para>While anyone can view the current values for campus type, only members with application
            specific manager or KR-SYS Technical Manager roles can create new campus types or edit
            existing values. This document does not route for approval.</para></note>
